Check our plan next week at http://tipton-county.com for revisions.

post_text:
As we prepare to begin school in August, we are asking parents of all returning students in 1st-12th grades to complete online registration in order to enroll for the 20-21 school year. This includes high school students who may have already selected or registered for their courses in the spring. When you complete online registration, you will be able to choose between face-to-face instruction or distance learning options for your child.

The enrollment period begins July 15th and ends July 31st.

Please visit our webpage at www.tipton-county.com for information and directions for completing online registration. Parent usernames and passwords were included with students' final report cards in May; however, if you need a username and password to complete the enrollment process, please contact your child's school for assistance.

Thank you for your support of Tipton County Schools. We look forward to seeing everyone in August!

August 14, 2019 at 5:59 PM ·

Our Superintendent of Schools, Dr. John Combs, hitched two rides on Ms. Paula Jenkins' bus from Atoka Elementary this afternoon. He wanted to see what kind of affect the heat had on students. He said he really enjoyed the ride. The kids asked him what a Superintendent does, and he said, "I'm the one who decides if you get a snow day or not." One little girl immediately showed him her "snow dance." Good job, Dr. Combs! :)

post_text:
A message from Dr. Combs - Good Afternoon Everyone. Today I was made aware of a situation that appears to be trending on social media involving some of our middle and high school students. Through the use of Snap Chat, inappropriate pictures of students are being shared on bogus accounts. Our concern has been shared with local law enforcement and because this information is happening outside of school, we are communicating with parents to make sure you know to be vigilant.

As appropriate, we encourage you to speak with your child about his or her cell phone usage, picture sharing, and social media citizenship.

Have a great evening and thank you for being a part of the Tipton County School system.
